text: I wanted to try him with extra combat steps since it would give you double sac and the first one sticks around for the second swing. Add in any kind of double strike or damage doubler and you can probably one shot the table each turn. How to do that is really tricky. Sure on occasion you'd have Rotting Regisaur and Traxos out, but getting enough efficient sac fodder seems really unlikely. Yeah, Sneak Attack and things like Into the Breach or Unearth might help, but the density of those effects you'd need is hard.

X amount of extra combat cards, X amount of big sacc fodder, X amount of ways to recur or cheat them out, X amount of ways to grant double strike or double damage, etc. I just couldn't figure out how to make it all work.
I think you fall prey to Paralysis via Analysis, <@U4V5EHQ2G>. I suspect you miss out on trying strategies that work better in execution than they seem on paper.
Maybe, but this is kinda how I tend to build decks, and the too many moving parts thing is often a real issue.
Sure but the moving parts means there are a lot of knobs to turn and tune.
I do put these things together in deck builders and test play them out
